{"start":[0,770,2040,3780,5690,7710,10310,12640,16950,20720,23740,25010,26690,28550,32310,36510,37130,38430,41480,42250,42985,43960,45910,49100,50906,51880,55470,58230,61800,65970,68910,70840,73980,75820,78460,81520,85370,88350,91450,93050,96990,98640,100040,103420,107220,110830,114890,117440,120810,125180,126500,128389,131015,134250,137200,139620,143990,146750],"end":[770,2040,3780,5690,7710,10310,12640,16950,20720,23740,25010,26690,28550,32310,36510,37130,38430,41480,42250,42985,43960,45910,49100,50906,51880,55470,58230,61800,65970,68910,70840,73980,75820,78460,81520,85370,88350,91450,93050,96990,98640,100040,103420,107220,110830,114890,117440,120810,125180,126500,128389,131015,134250,137200,139620,143990,146750,148000],"text":["","DAN KLEIN: Here's something else that you can do that's a","variant of local search.","These are called genetic algorithms.","Genetic algorithms are a kind of local search.","You got, in this case, not one hypothesis, but you've got a","hypothesis population.","You've got a bunch of hypotheses, and rather than just locally improving all","of them, which in genetic algorithms nomenclature is just mere mutation,","you're just mutating these things, they would say, mutation's not enough.","We've got to do more stuff.","We've got to make it even more like biology here.","So there's a natural selection metaphor.","You keep the best end hypotheses at each step, but you do more than that.","So in addition to just keeping the best one, then you find pairs and you","do crossover.","Essentially, you mate them.","You take hypotheses, and you breed hypotheses.","Here's what it looks like.","You have this robot.","You have this robot.","Up comes some weird hypothesis robot.","And then, in addition to breeding them, which is called crossover, you","then mutate them as well, which is what we were doing all","along in local search.","So it's a little bit more complicated, but it gets out a few more ideas that","might actually be these kinds of ridge operators.","So the selection part, that's basically just like going uphill.","The mutation part, that's basically looking around in your neighborhood.","Although mutation and selection look a lot like local search, we have to","think really hard about this crossover operation.","What does it mean to take two hypotheses and combine them?","Well, that's really the key.","That might be what gets you out of a local optimum.","And well, it might look like this.","In n-queens, we might say, well, here's one hypothesis, and maybe this","hypothesis has basically got the left half of the board right.","And here's another hypothesis, and maybe this hypothesis has basically","got the right half of the board right.","And if we mutate them, we're just going to move one piece at a time and","maybe both of them are pretty far.","But if only we combine them.","We take the left half from one, right half of the other, we get this new","species of queen solution, and suddenly we're solved, maybe.","And so here, crossover makes sense because we've got a way of encoding","the solution where really to have the prefix of one and the suffix of the","other actually makes sense.","This kind of crossover doesn't make sense when your solutions aren't","naturally encoded like this, or where a good left half and a good right half","don't really work together.","And you can imagine some of those problems here.","It could be that the left half is perfectly good, and the right have is","perfectly good, but they both use the bottom of the board, and then the","crossover would not be effective.","One more thing to say about these variance of local search.","They're very powerful in practice, but they're also pretty easy to misuse.","So for things like genetic algorithms, they're very often misapplied.",""]}